https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/1998/04/29/prosecutors-outline-kaczynskis-motives/3650b432-6efb-4ad7-96ef-8587fc6a56e0/
	PROSECUTORS OUTLINE KACZYNSKI'S MOTIVES

	In his own hand, convicted Unabomber Theodore J. Kaczynski wrote that he believed in nothing but "personal revenge," that he wanted to kill, not because of his love of nature, but his hatred of people, according to material released by federal prosecutors today.

	...In 1971, seven years before his first bomb, Kaczynski stated in his journal: "My motive for doing what I am going to do is simply personal revenge. I do not expect to accomplish anything by it."

	In another entry, Kaczynski wrote that he did not believe in "the cult of nature worshippers or wilderness worshippers," that "I am perfectly happy to litter in parts of the woods that are of no use to me." He, himself, tossed cans in the forests and poached game.

	He expresses little remorse in his writings, instead chiding himself for being "programmed" by society and "chickening out" when he wanted to kill. From an entry dated Sept. 15, 1980, "Guilty feelings? Yes, a little. . . . I am definitely glad to have done what I have."

	Kaczynski also did much to avoid apprehension, wearing disguises, sandpapering away fingerprints and going so far as to insert in one of his bombs a hair that he collected in a public rest room.

	Moreover, despite promising to stop sending bombs if his manifesto were published, his cabin contained the materials to make more bombs, including 40 pipes, rigged alarm clocks, 23 identical initiating devices, lists of potential victims with their home addresses and a handwritten manual entitled "How to Kill an Exxon Exec." A fully armed, powerful bomb was also found, the package ready for delivery, with a label stating it contained a tool commonly used in the aircraft industry. It lacked only an address. 



