	...The farmers will probably do all right, they say. Increased levels of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere makes plants happy, at least in the laboratory. Things grow well in warm weather.

	..."We did not forsee that people would dumbly suffer and so we did not use a 'dumb-people scenario.' We assumed people would adapt. We assumed people don't have feet of clay," said panel chairman Paul Waggoner, an agronomist and meterologist at the Connecticut Agricultural Experiment Station in New Haven.


